# Flow Design Standards

> **Review-time mechanical checklist:** For first-pass flow review items (bulkification risk, fault paths, null safety, infinite-loop prevention, entry conditions, etc.), see `.cursor/skills/sf-review-checklist-reference/SKILL.md` Section 11 — this rule defines *design standards*; the checklist defines *review checks*.

## Shared Metadata Hygiene

> For cross-cutting metadata hygiene (API version, description, package.xml), see `sf-metadata-standards-rule.mdc`.

## Bulkification Safety

- Record-triggered flows execute once per record by default. Flag any flow element that performs DML on unrelated objects inside a loop — this creates hidden N×DML patterns when invoked in bulk.
- Apex Action or subflow elements that perform DML must not be placed inside a Loop element.

## Fault Paths

- Every DML element, callout element, and subflow invocation must have a configured Fault connector — do not rely on the default "uncaught fault" behavior.

## Null Safety

- Variables used in decision conditions must be initialized or null-safe (`{!var} != null` checks present before use).

## Infinite Loop Prevention

- Record-triggered flows that update the triggering record must include a condition or entry check to prevent re-triggering (e.g., a prior-value check on the entry condition).

## Entry Conditions

- Record-triggered flows must have specific entry conditions — do not use "Always" unless intentional and justified in the description.

## Callout Restrictions

- Callout elements (HTTP, External Service) are not supported in after-save record-triggered flows. Flag for async refactor if found.

## Metadata Hygiene

- API version must match project standard (66.0).
- Flow must have a meaningful description explaining its purpose and trigger conditions.
- Set a meaningful `interviewLabel` for debugging purposes.
- `<status>Active</status>` only for flows ready for deployment. New flows in development should be `Inactive` or `Draft`.
- Record-triggered flows must specify `<triggerType>` explicitly (`RecordAfterSave` or `RecordBeforeSave`).
- API names use PascalCase (no `__c` suffix).
- Label must be verb-first and describe the action (e.g., "Assign Tier on Member Update").
